Document: OpenXRSpatialCapabilityConfigurationPlaneTracking  
Path: godot/classes/class_openxrspatialcapabilityconfigurationplanetracking.rst  
Summary: Methods for querying enabled components and spatial capability support in OpenXR plane tracking configurations.  

- PackedInt64Array get_enabled_components() const: Returns the components enabled by this configuration. Note: Only valid after this configuration was used to create a spatial context.  
- bool supports_labels(): Returns true if plane semantic label component is supported (only valid after OpenXR session starts). Query using OpenXRSpatialComponentPlaneSemanticLabelList data object.  
- bool supports_mesh_2d(): Returns true if mesh 2D component is supported (only valid after OpenXR session starts). Query using OpenXRSpatialComponentMesh2DList data object.  
- bool supports_polygons(): Returns true if polygon 2D component is supported (only valid after OpenXR session starts). Query using OpenXRSpatialComponentPolygon2DList data object.